		{"type":"text","text":"The problems: \n- Individuals and subgrops have differing views of truth on the world\n- Truth comes in varying levels of reliability\n- Importance of certain facts are weighted differently by different subgroups\n\nThese problems lead to diagreements when in reality, using simple logic gates and weightings could resolve the problems above, or at least pinpoint in an exact manner where a difference arises.\n\nWe will use this reductive framework from the field of mathematics called a **formal system**.\n\nA formal system is composed of symbols, finite sequences of symbols, and rules for sequences. \n\nWith this system, decisions remain (1) human understandable (as opposed to decision making via LLMs) and (2) based on foolproof logic. 1 is essential for maintaining consensual decisions with humans in the loop. 2 is possible because **uncertainty (from the unknown future and feelings) is abstracted away into contained variables.**\n","id":"3e4b1caa1adad2de","x":-254,"y":-275,"width":994,"height":895},
